The paper discusses the use of approximate message passing algorithms in graphical models, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), and optimization (cs.MM). The paper also focuses on structured sparsity problems, which are a common topic in signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI).
